        <num>CCP 4630</num>
        <heading>4630.  Partition in kind when defendant appears and prays therefor</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 4630.  Partition in kind when defendant appears and prays therefor
If the property sought to be partitioned is divisible in kind, and the defendant timely answers through counsel of his own selection and prays therefor, the court shall render judgment ordering the partition to be made in kind, under the applicable provisions of Chapter 1 of this Title.</p>
        </content>
